[6] Cholera - Equatorial Guinea (Bioko)
Date: Fri, 25 Feb 2005
From: Irene Lai <iwlai@attglobal.net>


We have received information from reliable sources of an outbreak of
suspected cholera in Equatorial Guinea that began in the 1st week of Feb
2005. More than 400 people with severe diarrhea and dehydration have been
hospitalized in Malabo. At least 2 cases have been confirmed as cholera,
and a number of deaths have occurred. Suspected cases on the mainland in
Bata have been reported too.

[Malabo, the capital, is located on Bioko Island off the coast of the
mainland. - Mod.LL]

--
Irene Lai
International SOS
<iwlai@attglobal.net>

