[7] Cholera - Brazil (Pernambuco)
Date: Fri, 24 Feb 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Program of 41st Congress of the Brazilian Society for Tropical
Medicine, (6-10 Mar 2005), Florianopolis, Santa Catarina, Brazil [edited]
<http://www.medtropfloripa2005.com.br/programatotal.html>


On 1 Feb 2005, the State Secretary of Health of Pernambuco confirmed a
report of a case of cholera from the municipality of Sao Bento do Una, in a
rural region of the state. The news report did not give the identity of the
strain of cholera involved.

The program of this congress lists the following paper:
Alessandro Pecego Martins Romano (DF) -- 1st notice of the isolation, since
2001, of toxigenic _Vibrio cholerae_ O1 Ogawa in an outbreak of acute
diarrhea, in Sao Bento de Una, Pernambuco. This is the same strain that was
originally imported to South America in 1991. Cholera serotype El Tor
biotype Ogawa came into Brazil from Peru in 1991, possibly by travelers
along the Amazon.

